Online Learning Tools






Online Learning Tools
Student tools and resources needed for online and hybrid learning.





            Quote
          Heading link



 
Copy link




Technology Solutions is dedicated to student success and providing the resources and support needed to succeed in hybrid learning environments.






            Shortcuts
          Heading link



 
Copy link












                            Basic Requirements
                    

                Basic requirements and technology tools needed for online and hybrid learning.
            












                            Education Technology
                    

                Blackboard Learn, VoiceThread, Respondus, and other Ed Tech tools students may need to use for courses.
            












                            Virtual Computer Lab
                    

                Access specialized software remotely from your personal devices.
            










            Other Resources
          Heading link



 
Copy link




Cloud Storage
Cloud Storage are used for file storage and file sharing. UIC Students have access to Box, Google Drive and OneDrive.
Equipment Lending
Equipment lending for short-term including laptops, projectors, wi-fi hotspots, camcorders, and more. The COVID-19 long-term loan term equipment lending program is available to students in need of a laptop or hotspot.
Hosting Meetings Online
Host meetings online and meet with classmates and peers using Google Meet, Microsoft Teams, or Zoom for communicating and collaborating online.
Software & Licensing
UIC licensing agreements often allow licensed software to be used both on-campus and on personal computers.









